perm_montecarlo is an open-source, cross-platform c++ library performing montecarlo simulations of self-avoiding walks.
Includes rosenbluth sampling, and PERM (Prune and Enriched Rosenbluth Method. It allows to control the amount of nearest neighbors, in 2D and 3D.

